President Donald J. Trump announced his intent to nominate Amanda Wood Laihow as a Member of the Occupational Safety and Health Review Commission. Laihow currently serves as the Chief Counsel to Chairman James J. Sullivan, Jr. at the Occupational Safety and Health Review Commission. She has also worked as the Director of Labor and Employment Policy for the National Association of Manufacturers and served in legal roles for the United States Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs Committee and the General Services Administration. Laihow holds a J.D. from the University of Maine School of Law and a B.A. in Political Science from the University of New Hampshire.

President Trump also announced his intent to appoint Almo J. Carter as a Commissioner of the United States Parole Commission. Additionally, he announced his intent to appoint several individuals as Members of the Commission on Presidential Scholars and the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. Lastly, President Trump appointed Kirstjen Nielsen as a Member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council.